Use while for conditions.
Use for when the no of times we have to loop is known.
Whenever we invoke a method on an obj it returns a new obj.
count on array counts the instance of each obj passed to it on whole.
count on string counts the instance of each letter of the string passed to it.
.find is called on an array, if the record is +nt in the array it returns the first occurence else nill.
Array is an ordered integer indexed collection of objects.
A hash is an unordered object indexed collection of objects.
Value of all the instance variables is nil.
Values to an instance ariable can be assigned or read only via a method.